<br>
I probably sound too harsh, but I've seen what EQ has done to people and its really amazing a &quot;game&quot; can have so much hold onto your life.<br>
<br>
Think of it this way.  The vast majority of people that are in Ordo are so called casual gamers.   Playing 2-3 hours a night while doing some exping, some trade skills, talking with friends really isn't that big of a deal.  Compared to the people that log on right after work, play til they go to bed at 3 am, get up, work, etc.  Friday night is log on, play til late, saturday log on all day, sunday same thing.<br>
<br>
To them, the game has become their life.  <br>
<br>
I see nothign wrong with playing EQ as long as you don't get sucked in too far.  I know, I've been there, done that many times and keep getting sucked back in.  For me the only way to break it is to delete.  I've tried cancelling, but that didn't work.<br>
<br>
